            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "An IFSC unit claims a 100 percent deduction of business income under Section 80LA of the Income Tax Act 1961 for any 10 consecutive years out of 15, counted from the year it obtains registration from the International Financial Services Centres Authority. The claim needs a chartered accountant's report in Form 10CCF, filed along with a return submitted by the due date."
